Welcome to PPE Object detection-Tensorflow Object Detection API’s documentation!¶

  • Preparing the Workspace
    • Mount Google Drive
    • Download TensorFlow Model Garden
    • Install some required libraries and tools
    • Compile the Protobuf libraries
    • Set the environment
    • Build and Install setup.py
      • Setup.py consists of setup script for object_detection with TF2.0
    • Test the Installation
      • If all the installations were successful, you should see output similar to the one shown below.
  • Generate Tfrecords
  • generate_tfrecord module
  • Start TensorBoard
    • TensorBoard allows you to track and visualize various training metrics while training is ongoing.
    • Initially, you will get a message saying “No dashboards are active for the current data set”.
    • But once the training start, you will see various training metrics.

  • Export the Trained Model
    • We have finished training our model, it’s time to extract our saved_model. This saved_model will be used to perform object recognition.
      • cd into training demo and run the command
    • The model will be saved in exported-models/my_model
  • Convert a SavedModel to TFlite
  • TensorFlow Lite Metadata Writer API
    • Adding metadata to TensorFlow Lite models
    • TensorFlow Lite metadata provides a standard for model descriptions. The metadata is an important source of knowledge about what the model does and its input / output information.
    • The metadata consists of both
    • human readable parts which convey the best practice when using the model, and
    • machine readable parts that can be leveraged by code generators, such as the TensorFlow Lite Android code generator and the Android Studio ML Binding feature.
      • The ObjectDetector API expects a TFLite model with mandatory TFLite Model Metadata.
        • Import the required packages.
        • Create metadata writer and populate.
